      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine, renowned for its individual throttle bodies and Double VANOS variable valve timing. This example delivers a visceral driving experience via a 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory-calibrated limited-slip differential. Critical preventative maintenance has been performed, including a comprehensive rear subframe reinforcement and rod bearing replacement to ensure structural and internal longevity. The chassis remains taut with upgraded bushings, while the suspension geometry provides the precise turn-in and lateral stability expected of the M-division. While the exterior shows minor road wear consistent with its age, the mechanical synchronization and throttle response are exceptionally sharp, making this a turn-key performance machine for the discerning driver.",
